elsey%20Vlamis%20%3C%2Fa%3Efor%20developments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMonday%20opened%20with%20jury%20selection%2C%20and%20the%20judge%20peppered%20over%2050%20potential%20jurors%20with%20questions%20about%20their%20investing%20experience%20after%20%26quot%3Bmini%20opening%20statements%26quot%3B%20from%20both%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20prosecutors%20told%20potential%20jurors%20it%20was%20a%20case%20involving%20%26quot%3BTwitter%2C%20tweets%2C%20and%20trading.%26quot%3B%20They%20said%20Left%20used%20his%20website%2C%20TV%20appearances%2C%20and%20100%2C000-strong%20Twitter%20following%20to%20manipulate%20markets%2C%20arguing%20he%20could%20send%20a%20stock%20price%20down%20with%20a%20single%20post.%20%26quot%3BTweets%20were%20essential%20to%20defendant's%20scheme%2C%26quot%3B%20Assistant%20US%20Attorney%20Andrew%20Roach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdam%20Fee%2C%20a%20lawyer%20for%20Left%2C%20said%20the%20defense%20would%20prove%20that%20Left%20%26quot%3Bonly%20shared%20his%20honestly%20held%20opinions%20about%20the%20stock%20market.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20the%20case%20is%20not%20about%20whether%20Left%20was%20right%20or%20wrong%2C%20but%20about%20whether%20he%20believed%20what%20he%20said%20when%20he%20said%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20off%20the%20bat%2C%20several%20jurors%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20potential%20bias%20or%20shared%20negative%20views%20about%20the%20stock%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20potential%20juror%20said%20he%20already%20had%20an%20opinion%20about%20the%20case%20after%20the%20openings%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20pundits.%26quot%3B%20Another%20said%20she%20had%20family%20who%20lost%20money%20in%20the%20stock%20market%20after%20listening%20to%20the%20opinions%20of%20others%20online.%20One%20potential%20juror%20who%20said%20he%20previously%20worked%20as%20a%20floor%20trader%20at%20the%20Chicago%20Board%20of%20Trade%20was%20dismissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%