%20multi-billion-dollar%20partnership%20between%20Microsoft%20and%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20key%20dynamic%20in%20Musk's%20lawsuit%20against%20Sam%20Altman%20and%20OpenAI.%20According%20to%20Musk%2C%20Altman%20joined%20in%20%26quot%3Blooting%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20by%20turning%20a%20nonprofit%20meant%20to%20benefit%20humanity%20into%20a%20goliath%20that%20made%20billions%20through%20its%20relationship%20with%20the%20Big%20Tech%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella's%20testimony%20seemed%20to%20mostly%20work%20against%20Musk.%20He%20showed%20jurors%20an%20email%20in%20which%20Musk%20thanks%20Nadella%20for%20financial%20and%20computing%20support%20for%20OpenAI%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20also%20told%20jurors%20that%20Musk%20never%20complained%20as%20Microsoft's%20lucrative%20licensing%20and%20revenue-sharing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-microsoft-partnership-agreement-changes-cloud-providers-agi-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epartnership%20with%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20grew%20and%20grew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Nadella%20stepped%20down%20from%20the%20witness%20stand%2C%20Musk's%20lawyers%20called%20Ilya%20Sutskever%2C%20an%20OpenAI%20cofounder%20who%20left%20after%20a%20power%20struggle%20that%20led%20to%20Altman%20temporarily%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-shock-firing-from-openai-just-became-bigger-mystery-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estepping%20down%20as%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Nadella%2C%20in%20his%20own%20testimony%2C%20had%20called%20the%20event%20%26quot%3Bamateur%20city.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESutskever%20wrapped%20up%20Musk's%20side%20of%20the%20case%2C%20and%20Altman's%20and%20OpenAI's%20legal%20team%20began%20presenting%20their%20case%20with%20OpenAI%20board%20chairman%20Bret%20Taylor%2C%20who%20repeatedly%20told%20jurors%20that%20the%20company%20remained%20dedicated%20to%20saving%20humanity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20four%20key%20takeaways%20from%20Nadella's%20testimony%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226598%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Satya%20Nadella%20in%20court%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a025864e1443b8dc48e411b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESatya%20Nadella%20in%20court%3Cp%3EKarl%20Mondon%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225ac27ac0-ed21-44e1-ab0e-607e7116ad7d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMusk%20was%20all%20in%20on%20working%20with%20Microsoft%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20questioning%20by%20a%20Microsoft%20lawyer%2C%20Nadella%20made%20the%20point%20that%20Musk%2C%20who%20had%20yet%20to%20quit%20OpenAI%2C%20had%20in%202016%20welcomed%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20eventual%20%2413%20billion%20Microsoft-OpenAI%20partnership%20that%20Musk%20is%20now%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20took%20a%20%2415%20million%20loss%2C%20Nadella%20told%20jurors%2C%20by%20letting%20OpenAI%20use%20its%20Azure%20cloud%20system%20%E2%80%94%20at%20a%20discount%20%E2%80%94%20to%20power%20the%20nascent%20technology%20behind%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20personally%20thanked%20Nadella%2C%20the%20CEO%20testified%2C%20in%20an%20August%202017%20email%2C%20after%20an%20OpenAI%20bot%20defeated%20an%20elite%20pro%20player%20in%20the%20world%20championship%20tournament%20for%20the%20game%20Dota%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVery%20much%20appreciated%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20told%20Nadella%20in%20the%20email%2C%20after%20Nadella%20congratulated%20the%20cofounders%20on%20their%20win.%20%26quot%3BWill%20make%20sure%20that%20people%20know%20about%20Microsoft's%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f3b64d3022d9b19bbff3ce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%20spent%20hours%20testifying%20in%20his%20case%20against%20OpenAI%20and%20Sam%20Altman.%3Cp%3EBenjamin%20Fanjoy%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b94836c4-0aa9-4ad1-af3f-9620fc0fba25%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'We%20have%20each%20others'%20phone%20number%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20took%20another%20hit%20at%20trial%20when%20a%20Microsoft%20lawyer%20asked%20Nadella%20if%20Musk%20ever%20complained%20to%20him%20about%20the%20partnership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20said%20he%20heard%20no%20complaints%20%E2%80%94%20not%20when%20the%20revenue-sharing%20partnership%20with%20OpenAI%20was%20announced%20in%20July%202019%2C%20and%20not%20even%20when%20news%20broke%20in%202023%20that%20Microsoft's%20investment%20stake%20had%20just%20risen%20by%20%2410%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Musk%20knew%20how%20to%20reach%20out%2C%20Nadella%20told%20jurors%2C%20noting%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20each%20other's%20phone%20numbers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20testimony%20could%20help%20OpenAI%20and%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20have%20claimed%20at%20trial%20that%20Musk%20only%20began%20complaining%20about%20the%20partnership%20when%20he%20filed%20the%202024%20lawsuit%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defendants%20in%20the%20trial%20%E2%80%94%20OpenAI%2C%20cofounders%20Altman%20and%20Greg%20Brockman%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20%E2%80%94%20are%20hoping%20to%20convince%20jurors%20that%20Musk%2C%20who%20announced%20his%20rival%20chatbot%2C%20xAI%2C%20later%20that%20year%2C%20is%20just%20a%20sore%20loser%20who%20is%20trying%20to%20take%20down%20his%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225311%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a02361ee1443b8dc48e3fee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESam%20Altman%20attending%20jury%20selection%20on%20April%2030%3Cp%3EJOSH%20EDELSON%20%2F%20AFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2208ed14eb-d610-4488-8b3e-5411a36e1243%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Above%2C%20below%2C%20around'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENadella%20was%20also%20asked%20about%20a%20trenchant%20remark%20he%20made%20to%20New%20York%20magazine%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Altman's%20brief%2C%20November%202023%20ouster%20from%20the%20helm%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20an%20event%20that%20threatened%20OpenAI's%20existence%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20OpenAI%20disappeared%20tomorrow%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20told%20the%20magazine%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20all%20the%20IP%20rights%20and%20all%20the%20capability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Microsoft's%20intellectual%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20below%20them%2C%20above%20them%2C%20around%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20said%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20a%20statement%20quickly%20hailed%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-satya-nadella-openai-baller-quote-new-war-slogan-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Ba%20baller%20quote%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%26quot%3Ba%20new%20war%20slogan%26quot%3B%20by%20some%20of%20the%20Microsoft%20CEO's%20Silicon%20Valley%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20side%20may%20try%20to%20use%20the%20statement%20to%20support%20his%20contention%20that%20he%20made%20a%20%2438%20million%20charitable%20donation%20to%20OpenAI%20during%20the%20company's%20early%20years%2C%20only%20to%20see%20Altman%20and%20cofounder%20Greg%20Brockman%20betray%20their%20promise%20to%20keep%20the%20company%20solely%20nonprofit.%20Microsoft%20and%20OpenAI%20are%20now%20%26quot%3Ba%20market-paralyzing%20gorgon%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20on%20the%20stand%20Monday%2C%20Nadella%20defended%20his%20%26quot%3Babove%2C%20below%2C%20around%26quot%3B%20statement%2C%20saying%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20calm%20any%20concerns%20over%20Altman's%20ouster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20goes%20back%20to%20me%20trying%20to%20comm